724488f-a.text:
Bloomingdale (Dutch) Reformed Church, West End Avenue, west side, between 106th and 107th Streets, the northernmost block of West End Avenue. The view is across Straus Park, a little triangle formed by the intersection of Broadway, West End Avenue, and 106th Street.

The church edifice and two apartment buildings are quite new as shown, erected since 1902: and the church will be demolished about 1915, to be replaced by another 12-story apartment building. 1906.

Brown Brothers, Photographers.
